\title{bayescomp: Bayesian Hierarchical Comparison of Computational Method Benchmarks}
\description{
A targets-integrated workflow for fitting Bayesian hierarchical models to computational method benchmarks. Supports negative binomial (count data), Gamma (timing), Bernoulli (success), and Student-t (signed errors) families with random intercepts per test system. Provides automated family selection, weakly informative prior defaults, convergence diagnostics, LOO-CV, posterior predictive checks, and publication-quality effect summaries. Built on 'brms' and 'cmdstanr'.
